700347f-a.title: Bronx: 230th Street (West) - Riverdale Avenue
700347f-a.text:
West 230th Street (foreground, not seen), north side, east from Riverdale Ave. to Tibbett Ave. In the center background appear the rears of frame houses facing on the west side of Corlear Ave. Across the same are visible the rears of the St. John's Roman Catholic Church (right) and the Protestant Episcopal Church of the Mediator, both facing on the west side of Kingsbridge Ave., between West 230th and West 231st
Streets.
October 27, 1927.
P. L. Sperr.
